!! Tests

Unit tests live in `test/`. Run from the plugin's test-edition:

```
cd dev-wiki/plugins/rimir/present/test-edition
TIDDLYWIKI_PLUGIN_PATH=/home/mrichter/projects/tw5-cc/dev-wiki/plugins \
  npx tiddlywiki . --test
```

The `TIDDLYWIKI_PLUGIN_PATH` is needed because `tiddlywiki.info` references `rimir/present` by short name — TW can only resolve that from a directory it's been told contains plugins.

Current coverage:

* `test-grid.js` — `_buildGrid` partition rules (consecutive grouping, solo buckets for missing/blank section-field, custom field name, empty input).

The interactive parts (keydown handlers, DOM lifecycle, link interception) aren't unit-tested — exercise them manually after changes.

!! Manual checklist

Before bumping a release, run through:

# Open a presentation via the mindmap ''▶ Play'' button → overlay appears, first slide visible, HUD shows `1/N · 1/M`.
# `→` / `←` walk between sections; `↑` / `↓` walk within a section. Counter updates.
# `Space` linearly advances down-then-right; `Backspace` reverses.
# `Home` jumps to first slide; `End` to last.
# Click a wikitext link inside a slide → deep-dive: breadcrumb shows depth, stage re-renders.
# `Esc` pops one level; click `⌂` to pop everything at once.
# `N` shows the notes panel (or empty placeholder); reopen on next slide shows that slide's notes.
# `?` shows help; toggling off shows the slide again.
# `×` button closes the deck and clears `$:/state/rimir/mindmap/present-open`.
# Shift+F2 inside the mindmap canvas opens the active presentation. F5 / Shift+F5 stay as browser reload — F2 alone is taken by the edit-node intercept, so the player layers Shift on top.
# Open mindmap, switch the modebar to ''Presentation'' on a deck with at least one slide — both the header Play button AND the small ▶ next to the dropdown become visible. Switch back to ''Body'' — both hide.
# Open a deck with no slides → both Play buttons hidden, Shift+F2 no-ops.

!! Versioning

Standard rules apply — patch bumps for fixes / small additions, minor bumps when adding new attributes or layouts that other plugins might depend on. Always update `changelog.tid` alongside any `plugin.info` version bump.

